{
  "stem": "3848.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Well, that's one of those things that we had to go through.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But I was physically strong otherwise, besides the malaria.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We worked there until the war ended.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The war, I know-- I found out later that the war ended in 1945.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, my city was liberated by the Russians in 1944, but I didn't know about that.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they wouldn't let us out of there anyhow, because they needed whatever help they got from us to work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at the end, in '46, the Russian government decided to send all the Polish people back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't tell the Russian people that I was born in Rowne, because the city of Rowne, still today, remains a Russian city.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if I would have said that the city of Rowne was where I was born, they would have sent me back to Rowne, and that means I couldn't get out of Russia anyhow.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wanted to get out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I told them that I was born in the city of Warsaw, which I never saw before.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the documents that I gave them in 1946-- the beginning of 1946 in the city of Aktiubinsk-- they allowed me to travel to Aktiubinsk.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It wasn't easy to go the 200 kilometers traveling.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, it was winter time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I showed them a picture that I had with me, was left of a Zionist organization from before the war.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have a copy of it that I found in the United States right here, which had epaulets.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Russians, at the beginning, were removing those epaulets.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Their soldiers didn't have epaulets in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Just later on they put them back.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
